#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:1
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:5
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:7
msgid ""
"**To use the web application:** a modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, or "
"Safari). No installation required — the editor runs entirely in the browser "
"at [cpsv-editor.open-regels.nl]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:9
msgid "**To run the editor locally:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:11
msgid "Node.js 14 or higher"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:12
msgid "npm"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:16
msgid "Local installation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:18
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/your-org/cpsv-editor.git\n"
"cd cpsv-editor\n"
"npm install\n"
"npm start"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:25
msgid "The application opens at `http://localhost:3000`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:27
msgid "To build a production bundle:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:29
msgid "npm run build"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:33
msgid "The `build/` directory contains the static files ready for deployment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:37
msgid "Creating your first service definition"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:39
msgid "The typical workflow for a new service definition follows these steps:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:41
msgid ""
"**Fill in Service Details** — Enter the service identifier, official name, "
"description, and sector. The identifier becomes the base for all RDF URIs in "
"the output, so choose something stable and descriptive (e.g. `aow-"
"leeftijdsbepaling`)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:43
msgid ""
"**Add Organisation** — Enter the competent authority. The geographic "
"jurisdiction (`cv:spatial`) is mandatory."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:45
msgid ""
"**Link Legal Resource** — Enter the BWB ID of the governing legislation "
"(e.g. `BWBR0002221`). The editor validates the format and constructs the ELI "
"URI."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:47
msgid ""
"**Define Rules** *(optional)* — Add temporal rules that implement the legal "
"resource."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:49
msgid ""
"**Add Parameters** *(optional)* — Add configurable constants used by the "
"rules."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:51
msgid ""
"**Add Policy (CPRMV)** *(optional)* — Import or enter normative rules "
"extracted from the legislation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:53
msgid ""
"**Validate** — Click the **Validate** button to check for errors. Missing "
"mandatory fields are highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:55
msgid ""
"**Download TTL** — Click **Download TTL** to export the compliant Turtle "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:64
msgid "Importing an existing file"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:66
msgid "If you have an existing `.ttl` file:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:68
msgid "Click **Import TTL File** in the header."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:69
msgid "Select the file."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:70
msgid "All tabs populate automatically from the imported data."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:71
msgid "Edit the fields as needed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:72
msgid "Download the updated Turtle."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:76
msgid "Clearing the editor"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cgetting-started.md:78
msgid ""
"Click **Clear** in the header to reset all fields. A confirmation dialog "
"prevents accidental data loss."
msgstr ""
